3. Define for each relevant (in this context) well-being dimension two dfs: one where researchers positively refer to the topic/dimension and one with a negative reference to it¶

In [15]:
# define the relevant well-being related topics for each dimension
relationships_topics = [21, 72, 87, 114, 192, 195, 196, 291, 604, 1590, 4849, 6390, 7395, 11438, 11733, 19447, 22248]
accomplishment_topics = [26, 58, 116, 232, 5952, 9662, 13325, 19486, 22291]
economic_security_topics = [26, 130, 303, 543, 1166, 2014, 3158, 14012, 17765, 19010, 24057]
physical_health_topics = [76, 127, 144, 152, 1956, 2014, 6407, 13568, 13599, 22492, 24086]
work_environment_topics = [87, 184, 193, 539, 714, 1225, 2022, 4615]
mindset_topics = [103, 679, 1265, 3130, 12464, 14137, 16179, 18289, 18300, 21197, 21203, 22011, 22291]
engagement_topics = [346, 2917]

# create a timelines df with probs >.5
timelines_topics_highprob = timelines_topics[timelines_topics["prob"] > 0.5]

# create df (filter) for each well-being dimension
relationships_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(relationships_topics)]
accomplishment_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(accomplishment_topics)]
economic_security_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(economic_security_topics)]
physical_health_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(physical_health_topics)]
work_environment_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(work_environment_topics)]
mindset_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(mindset_topics)]
engagement_df = timelines_topics_highprob[timelines_topics_highprob["topic"].isin(engagement_topics)]

# split the dfs in tweets with positive and negative affect
relationships_df_pos = relationships_df[relationships_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
relationships_df_neg = relationships_df[relationships_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]
accomplishment_df_pos = accomplishment_df[accomplishment_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
accomplishment_df_neg = accomplishment_df[accomplishment_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]
economic_security_df_pos = economic_security_df[economic_security_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
economic_security_df_neg = economic_security_df[economic_security_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]
physical_health_df_pos = physical_health_df[physical_health_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
physical_health_df_neg = physical_health_df[physical_health_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]
work_environment_df_pos = work_environment_df[work_environment_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
work_environment_df_neg = work_environment_df[work_environment_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]
mindset_df_pos = mindset_df[mindset_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
mindset_df_neg = mindset_df[mindset_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]
engagement_df_pos = engagement_df[engagement_df["pos_sent"] > 0.5]
engagement_df_neg = engagement_df[engagement_df["neg_sent"] > 0.5]

3. Aggregate monthly and add the n values¶

In [16]:
# relationships
relationships_pos = relationships_df_pos[["created_at", "pos_sent"]]
n = relationships_pos.resample("M", on="created_at").size()
relationships_pos = relationships_pos.resample("M", on ="created_at").mean()
relationships_pos["n"] = n
relationships_pos["n_all"] = n_all

relationships_neg = relationships_df_neg[["created_at", "neg_sent"]]
n = relationships_neg.resample("M", on="created_at").size()
relationships_neg = relationships_neg.resample("M", on ="created_at").mean()
relationships_neg["n"] = n
relationships_neg["n_all"] = n_all

Let's add a column with the relative n values

In [17]:
relationships_pos["n_rel"] = relationships_pos["n"] / relationships_pos["n_all"]
relationships_neg["n_rel"] = relationships_neg["n"] / relationships_neg["n_all"]
accomplishment_pos["n_rel"] = accomplishment_pos["n"] / accomplishment_pos["n_all"]
accomplishment_neg["n_rel"] = accomplishment_neg["n"] / accomplishment_neg["n_all"]
economic_security_pos["n_rel"] = economic_security_pos["n"] / economic_security_pos["n_all"]
economic_security_neg["n_rel"] = economic_security_neg["n"] / economic_security_neg["n_all"]
physical_health_pos["n_rel"] = physical_health_pos["n"] / physical_health_pos["n_all"]
physical_health_neg["n_rel"] = physical_health_neg["n"] / physical_health_neg["n_all"]
work_environment_pos["n_rel"] = work_environment_pos["n"] / work_environment_pos["n_all"]
work_environment_neg["n_rel"] = work_environment_neg["n"] / work_environment_neg["n_all"]
mindset_pos["n_rel"] = mindset_pos["n"] / mindset_pos["n_all"]
mindset_neg["n_rel"] = mindset_neg["n"] / mindset_neg["n_all"]
engagement_pos["n_rel"] = engagement_pos["n"] / engagement_pos["n_all"]
engagement_neg["n_rel"] = engagement_neg["n"] / engagement_neg["n_all"]
